    Cry of Athena

    Gameplay engineer, AI developer& game physics engineer

    In the Cry of Athena project at Simulated Minds, I worked as a gameplay engineer, focusing on NPC locomotion, AI behavior tree development, and pathfinding. My role included designing and implementing realistic NPC movement, optimizing decision-making processes, and integrating physics-based gameplay elements.
